TASK: Add UTM parameter capture for the SPA.

CONTEXT: React SPA at /home/workspace/verdant-goods-store. Sprint 2 task S2-5.2. Uses wouter for routing. GA4 is installed.

STEPS:
1. Create a custom hook at /home/workspace/verdant-goods-store/client/src/hooks/useUTMParams.ts:
   - On mount, read URL search params for: utm_source, utm_medium, utm_campaign, utm_content, utm_term
   - If any UTM param exists, fire a gtag event with the params
   - Also store UTM params in sessionStorage for attribution across SPA navigation

2. Add the hook to the Router component in App.tsx:
   - Import and call useUTMParams() at the top of the Router function

3. The hook implementation:
   import { useEffect } from 'react';
   export function useUTMParams() {
     useEffect(() => {
       const params = new URLSearchParams(window.location.search);
       const utm = {
         source: params.get('utm_source'),
         medium: params.get('utm_medium'),
         campaign: params.get('utm_campaign'),
         content: params.get('utm_content'),
         term: params.get('utm_term'),
       };
       if (Object.values(utm).some(v => v !== null)) {
         sessionStorage.setItem('utm_params', JSON.stringify(utm));
         if (typeof window !== 'undefined' && (window as any).gtag) {
           (window as any).gtag('set', { ...utm });
         }
       }
     }, []);
   }

4. Report: files created and modified
